WITH ranked_billing AS (
    SELECT
        subscription_id,
        event_month,
        amount,
        ROW_NUMBER() OVER (PARTITION BY subscription_id, event_month ORDER BY event_id) AS rn
    FROM billing_events
),
deduplicated_billing AS (
    SELECT subscription_id, event_month, amount
    FROM ranked_billing
    WHERE rn = 1
),
active_subs AS (
    SELECT
        s.subscription_id,
        s.user_id,
        COALESCE(p.tier, 'Unknown') AS tier,
        COALESCE(c.industry, 'Unknown') AS industry
    FROM subscriptions s
    LEFT JOIN plans p ON s.plan_id = p.plan_id
    LEFT JOIN users u ON s.user_id = u.user_id
    LEFT JOIN companies c ON u.company_id = c.company_id
    WHERE s.status = 'active'
)
SELECT
    db.event_month AS month,
    a.tier,
    a.industry,
    COUNT(DISTINCT a.subscription_id) AS active_subscriptions,
    SUM(db.amount) AS total_mrr,
    COUNT(DISTINCT a.user_id) AS unique_users
FROM deduplicated_billing db
JOIN active_subs a ON db.subscription_id = a.subscription_id
GROUP BY db.event_month, a.tier, a.industry
ORDER BY db.event_month, a.tier, a.industry;
```","time":{"start":1771625498636,"end":1771625498636}}}
